latestPosts.caption:
Cosmo Man coverstar actor Ali Fazal (@alifazal9 ) has been making strides in both Bollywood and Hollywood of late. His most recent sighting was in Forget Me Not—part of @netflix_in ‘s four-episode series inspired by Satyajit Ray’s short stories, Ray. Read excerpts of Ali’s interview with Cosmo India below: 
.
Editor: Nandini Bhalla (@nandinibhalla )
Interviews By: Meghna Sharma( @sharmameghna)
Photographer: Rahul Jhangiani (@rahuljhangiani)
Photographer assistant: Azfar Khan (@afzarkhan94 )
Stylist: Who_wore_what_when (@who_wore_what_when)
Makeup: @makeupbykausha 
Hair @arbazshaikh6210
.
C: You had to postpone your wedding plans due to the pandemic. Do you plan to get married this year? 
AF: “We have put our plans on hold because every two months there is some scare. And it has been a horrible year for me, personally, as it has been for a lot of people. So we decided it is best to wait for a while. We will probably celebrate with close family and friends, and host a reception in Mumbai.”
 
C: How did you propose to Richa [Chadha]? Was it a big romantic gesture?
AF: “I did plan something grand for her. I remember we got three days off, and we had gone to the Maldives and the plan was to come back and ask her to marry me. It was some crazy helicopter thing, with things flying in the air, and probably a hundred people would have seen. So I was a little nervous. But while we were in the Maldives, I had planned a surprise dinner for her birthday...it was on an island, and we were in the middle of the ocean, so it was very romantic. And I was just sitting there and admiring the beautiful sky and I decided to propose in the moment—it was as clichéd as it could get. It is weird because that’s the kind of thing I used to mock my friends for. I’d tell them that this only happens in movies. But then I was like, ‘Screw it!’ and I just went ahead with something simple. I thought it was kind of cute.”
 .
